Who We Are?

IAmCare

ABN: 11 580 405 105

Mission - Why are we here for?

Luke 14 : 12 - 14

But when you give a feast, invite the poor, the crippled, the lame, the blind, and you will be blessed, because they cannot repay you.

John 9 : 1 - 3

As he passed by, he saw a man blind from birth. And his disciples asked him, Rabbi, who sinned, this man or his parents, that he was born blind? Jesus answered, It was not that this man sinned, or his parents, but that the works of God might be displayed in him.

our policy

Treat everyone uniquely, ensuring individual needs are met;

Create a welcoming, ability friendly, confidential and culturally appropriate environtment;

Recognize, value and respect the diversity of IAMCare's Workers, Clients and the families and communities they live;

Ensure Clients with diverse needs can access IAMCare's services and are free from stigma, discrimination and stereotyping;

Ensure IAMCare's services and supports are culturally appropriate and sensitive to confidentiality of personal diversity as determined by the Client;

At the direction of the Client, Identify and respond to the culture, values and beliefs of the Client.

Vision - What Guiding us?

Disability is a matter of perception. If you can do just one thing well, youre needed by someone.-Martina Navratilova

Requirements for Victorian Applicants

To be considered, you must have the below mandatory requirements to submit with your application. 
Current Police Check 
Working with Children Check (Employment)
A Disability Worker Exclusion Scheme Check
A current RTO provided First Aid Certificate (HLTAID003) 
A current RTO provided CPR Certificate (HLTAID001) 
A completed Application for Employment 
A signed Position Description 
A cover letter and resume, including 2 references 
Evidence of your eligibility to work within Australia (Australian Passport/Birth Certificate/Australian Citizenship Certificate or International Passport & Visa) 
A current Australian Drivers License 
If you have lived or worked overseas in the last 10 years, we will require a certified copy of an International Police Check, or evidence of having applied for one. This must cover the entire period you were overseas. 
Mandatory training as required by funding bodies (see section below)

IAMCare provides 24/7 personal and flexible support services for all ages: Toddlers, Teenagers and Adult! Talk to us and we can personalized a service for YOU!

IAMCare objective is to support every individual to accomplish YOUR individualized goal.

IAMCare can provide supports for YOU whether at home, hospital or outside for community access.

Caring is our priority!

We make sure children are learning while we are taking care of them!

Taking care of PWD is our passion with love and honesty.

item.content:encoded:
Recruitment

Helping people. Chasing lives.

Join IAMCare

Our need for manpower is constant and continues to evolve as we navigate this Coronavirus health crisis. If you are interested in serving to met essential service needs in the public, it's simple!

Requirements for Victorian Applicants

To be considered, you must have the below mandatory requirements to submit with your application. 
Current Police Check 
Working with Children Check (Employment)
A Disability Worker Exclusion Scheme Check
A current RTO provided First Aid Certificate (HLTAID003) 
A current RTO provided CPR Certificate (HLTAID001) 
A completed Application for Employment 
A signed Position Description 
A cover letter and resume, including 2 references 
Evidence of your eligibility to work within Australia (Australian Passport/Birth Certificate/Australian Citizenship Certificate or International Passport & Visa) 
A current Australian Drivers License 
If you have lived or worked overseas in the last 10 years, we will require a certified copy of an International Police Check, or evidence of having applied for one. This must cover the entire period you were overseas. 
Mandatory training as required by funding bodies (see section below)

Pre employment training required for all applicants:  
The below certificates/inductions are mandatory for all Disability Service Providers. To ensure that all IAMCARE clients are receiving quality services. All trainings below are free of charge.

NDIS Worker Orientation

NDIS Worker Induction

Zero Tolerance of Abuse

COVID-19 Infection Control

If you are interested for roles Supporting Clients funded by TAC we also require the following:

DHHS Do Food Safely

Basic of Infection Prevention Control

inspire greatness together

we connect unique perspectives

To build a better tomorrow.

Working at iamcare

Why IAMCARE?

Grow, collaborate and change the world for the better

Get the opportunity for personal and professional growth on an unprecedented scale. 

Social Responsibility

How we support our communities, our people and the future

We provide resources and financial support to causes around the world and encourage employee volunteerism.
